@MrShadowSmith I think as far as the show he would have worked better with Claire. but they had to shut that down to try to force Karen. Then they brought Elektra in, It's called bad writing, 

Claire's reason for not wanting to be with Matt was dumb, because she ended up with Luke Cage and was hanging out with Danny and Colleen. Karen isn't his MJ, Elektra is, whether she's toxic or not. Matt is toxic also. They are  trying to make Matt James Bond or Bruce Wayne with the ladies and that's not accurate at all. They did this with Arrow also. 

Karen should be dead. but they keeping her for the shippers and nostalgia. Heather is better for Matt. But Matt is being difficult keeping a secret, as if nobody knows already. Then we will have episodes of them fighting about it, just like the comics. We already been down this road with Foggy and Karen.  There is no Nelson Murdock and Page in the comics. They were just trying to keep her around. Heather and Karen are back for season 2. The shippers will want her with Frank also. Frank doesn't have a love interest, that doesn't work in his line of work. He tried with Beth in season 2. Elektra and Matt work good or bad because they are both skilled fighters and do similar work. Matt can be himself, no secrets. and Elektra doesn't need protection, she's the one of the best fighters in the Marvel universe.

